I can’t fetch RPC state from this shell, so I’m making the verifier state-driven at runtime: it will discover vulnerable routes, prefer draining existing gateway ETH if present, otherwise probe existing gateway balances of pre-existing mainnet tokens and only mark profit once value is actually realized. That keeps the PoC executable on the validator’s fork instead of depending on brittle hardcoded assumptions.
